##Find the derivatrive expression and slope of exercise A $f(x) = x ^ 2 $ \(f(x) = 3\)

exp_A <- expression(x ^ 2)
deriv_result_A <- deriv(exp_A, "x")
deriv_result_A
## expression({
##     .value <- x^2
##     .grad <- array(0, c(length(.value), 1L), list(NULL, c("x")))
##     .grad[, "x"] <- 2 * x
##     attr(.value, "gradient") <- .grad
##     .value
## })
x <- 3
m_result_A <- eval(deriv_result_A)
m_result_A
## [1] 9
## attr(,"gradient")
##      x
## [1,] 6

##Find the derivatrive expression and slope of exercise B

\(P(a) = 2(3a + 2)^4 - 5\) \(P(a) = 1.2\)

exp_b = expression(2 * (3 * a + 2)^4 - 5)
deriv_B <- deriv(exp_b, "a")
deriv_B
## expression({
##     .expr2 <- 3 * a + 2
##     .value <- 2 * .expr2^4 - 5
